Societe Generale Said to Name Hubert Preschez Head of French M&A

-- B y   J a c q u e l i n e   S i m m o n s
-- 
2011-04-08T10:26:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/societe-generale-said-to-name-hubert-preschez-head-of-french-m-a.html
Societe Generale (GLE)  SA,  France ’s
second-largest bank by market value, named Hubert Preschez head
of French mergers and acquisitions, according to two people
familiar with the situation.  Preschez, 40, joined the bank in September as a managing
director from JPMorgan Chase & Co. in France. He will continue
to report to Thierry d’Argent, global head of M&A at Societe
Generale, said the people, who declined to be identified.  D’Argent joined the Paris-based bank in May 2009 after
previously working at JPMorgan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jacqueline Simmons in Paris at 
 jackiem@bloomberg.net ; 